
Overview of verb rip

The verb rip has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                            
1. (8) rend, rip, rive, pull -- (tear or be torn violently; "The curtain ripped from top to bottom"; "pull the cooked chicken into strips")
2. (2) rip -- (move precipitously or violently; "The tornado ripped along the coast")
3. (2) rip -- (cut (wood) along the grain)
4. rip -- (criticize or abuse strongly and violently; "The candidate ripped into his opponent mercilessly")
